FBIS3-48761 "dreas019_a_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-019 Document Type:Daily Report 28 January 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Tokyo Signs for 119.6 Billion Yen Loans to India OW2401113294 Tokyo KYODO in English 1102 GMT 24 Jan 94 OW2401113294 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 24 KYODO -- The government signed an agreement Monday [24 January] to provide a total of 119.6 billion yen in loans to India, officials said. The loans are to fund six projects, including construction of a coal-burning power plant in western Bengal. The 2.6 percent loans are repayable over 30 years after a 10-year grace period, the officials said.
